      "step_index": 1,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Core scaffold:** a **phosphoramidate\u2013phosphoramidate (P\u2013N / P\u2013O\u2013P / P\u2013N)** system (two phosphoryl groups, P=O).\n- **Substituents:** multiple **isopropylamino** groups (`NC(C)C`) attached to phosphorus (i.e., **phosphoramidates**, not simple alkyl amines).\n- **Functional groups present:**\n  - **Phosphoryl groups (P=O) x2** \u2192 strongly polar, strong H-bond acceptors.\n  - **P\u2013NH\u2013 (phosphoramidate nitrogens) x4** \u2192 can be H-bond donors, but **basicity is strongly reduced** by adjacent phosphoryl.\n  - **No aromatic rings**, no heteroaromatic systems.\n- **Structural alerts for CYP2D6 inhibition:** typical alerts are **protonatable tertiary amines + aromatic/lipophilic rings** (quinidine-like). This molecule has **no aromatic rings** and **no tertiary amine**.",
      "tool_name": null,
