      "step_index": 2,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) REASON (why features affect CYP2D6 inhibition)\nCYP2D6 inhibitors commonly have:\n- A **basic nitrogen** (often pKa ~8\u201310) that is **protonated at pH 7.4**, enabling ionic interaction with acidic residues in the CYP2D6 active site (often described around Asp301), and\n- **One or more aromatic/lipophilic rings** to occupy hydrophobic pockets.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:42:43.330856+00:00"
    },
    {
